{
  "doc_id": "25074",
  "text": "The prognosis of patients with EPSCC is generally unfavourable as is the case for those with SCLC. This is due to an aggressive natural history of EPSCC -a course characterised by rapid local progression, early, widespread metastases and recurrence after treatment [CITATION_1] . The epidemiological and clinical literature describing EPSCC is relatively limited. One of the most recent and largest studies reported a series of 101 patients and found an overall median survival of 9.83 months after diagnosis [CITATION_2] .",
